Wash and dry all produce. Pat @chicken thighs{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and
season all over with @pepper{}. Sprinkle evenly all over with @cornstarch{2%tablespoon}.
Rub cornstarch into meat to moisten and evenly coat.

Quarter @lime{1}. Peel @cucumber{1}, then halve lengthwise. Scoop out seeds with a
#spoon{} and discard. Slice flesh into thin semicircles. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. In a #medium bowl{}, toss together
cucumber, scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Place @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{} in a #small pot{}.
Bring to a boil, then cover, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook
until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until meal is ready.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook
until surface is crisp and a deep golden brown, about ~{6%minutes} per side. While
chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @soy sauce{2%tablespoon},
@sesame oil{2%teaspoon} (save the rest for the next step),
@sugar{4%teaspoon}, and @sriracha{4%teaspoon}.

> TIP: Add the sriracha to taste—use all if you like it spicy or 3 tsp for mild
> heat.

Once chicken is done, remove from pan. Discard excess oil and let pan cool off
heat for about ~{30%seconds}. Add soy sauce mixture to pan and let bubble using
residual heat.

> TIP: If sauce doesn't bubble, heat pan over medium-low heat until it does.

Return chicken to pan and flip to coat. Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in
remaining @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, a squeeze of @lime{1}, and half the scallion
greens. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, chicken, and cucumber salad between plates. Drizzle with any remaining
sauce in pan. Sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon},
@Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste), and remaining scallion greens.
Serve with remaining lime quarters.